Adopt strategies, despite personnel limitations, so that planned projects by the LGU may be timely implemented within the budget year and completed within the stipulated time frames.

We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Accountant to prepare and submit the Monthly Trial Balance and Quarterly Financial Statements with complete Schedules and Annexes within the prescribed timeframe in accordance with the abovementioned existing rules and regulations;

Augment qualified personnel in the Accounting Unit to be able to generate timely accounting reports and ensure submission thereof within the reglementary period;

Take appropriate immediate remedial measures, such as augmenting the Municipal Accountant’s Office with personnel from other departments, especially during report preparation periods and/or allowing them to render overtime, subject to the availability of funds, in order to comply with the timely preparation and submission of the mandatory financial reports pursuant to mandated deadlines; and

Allow qualified plantilla personnel of the Municipal Accounting Office to attend trainings or seminars relative to their job assignments to equip them with the required knowledge and skills in order to improve their performance.

